<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Given that:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{log } A = {0.2815}, \quad \text{log } B = {0.2229}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Use logarithms to find the value of:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\frac{A}{B}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to 3 decimal places.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Use the quotient rule:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{log} \left(\frac{A}{B}\right) = \text{log } A - \text{log } B
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {0.2815} - {0.2229}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {0.0586}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Take the antilogarithm:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\frac{A}{B} = 10^{0.0586}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {1.144}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>1.144</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>